[SPEAKER_11]: OK.

91
00:16:07,690 --> 00:16:11,673
[SPEAKER_11]: So the recommended so the language is that a definition

92
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:19,546
[SPEAKER_11]: A building not owned or operated by a college or university that contains bedrooms primarily for students.

93
00:16:20,186 --> 00:16:24,770
[SPEAKER_11]: Student residents must be enrolled in an accredited post-secondary educational institution.

94
00:16:25,431 --> 00:16:34,838
[SPEAKER_11]: Bedrooms may be arranged around a common area with a kitchen, which is shared by individuals renting the bedrooms, or along a hall which provides access to a common kitchen space.

95
00:16:35,559 --> 00:16:41,304
[SPEAKER_11]: Other shared or common facilities include sanitary, bathing, recreation, laundry,

96
00:16:41,895 --> 00:16:47,517
[SPEAKER_11]: mail package rooms, storage, trash, and recycling, bicycle storage, and vehicular parking.

97
00:16:48,137 --> 00:16:53,880
[SPEAKER_11]: Bedrooms shall be rented on an annual basis or for an academic semester or a summer term.

98
00:16:54,580 --> 00:17:00,642
[SPEAKER_11]: Accessory uses may include fitness facilities, pools, parking areas, and similar facilities.

99
00:17:01,302 --> 00:17:07,545
[SPEAKER_11]: A lodging or boarding house is not a private dormitory, nor is a rental of single-family homes to students.

100
00:17:08,487 --> 00:17:14,388
[SPEAKER_11]: Now the way that this is sort of, this would actually be regulated by use standards.

101
00:17:15,008 --> 00:17:23,991
[SPEAKER_11]: And so now I'm gonna go down to in the document, the use standards purpose built.

102
00:17:26,331 --> 00:17:26,691
[SPEAKER_11]: Sorry.

103
00:17:30,292 --> 00:17:32,032
[SPEAKER_11]: So these are the standards for it.

104
00:17:33,633 --> 00:17:34,533
[SPEAKER_11]: Let me reset.

105
00:17:35,102 --> 00:17:42,945
[SPEAKER_11]: In addition to meeting all other standards of this article, the requirements of this section shall comply with the following standards.

106
00:17:43,165 --> 00:17:51,248
[SPEAKER_11]: So it would be within a mile of this college or university and I'll just state that all of the Boston Ave area that we have been looking at is within a mile.

107
00:17:51,828 --> 00:17:56,090
[SPEAKER_11]: At this time the use table is only yes or it's CDB.

108
00:17:57,390 --> 00:18:02,976
[SPEAKER_11]: So special permit CDB in the BA3, and it's currently no in the other zones.

109
00:18:03,437 --> 00:18:12,726
[SPEAKER_11]: But we wrote this just in a way that if somebody tried to use it in another zone, this would, we felt this would cover that, those uses as well.

110
00:18:13,487 --> 00:18:16,410
[SPEAKER_11]: But we were not recommending it in the BA1 or 2 areas.

111
00:18:19,398 --> 00:18:27,560
[SPEAKER_11]: So we start with a minimum number of beds, no fewer than 150 beds, and no more than two beds per bedroom.

112
00:18:28,100 --> 00:18:44,724
[SPEAKER_11]: And the intention here is that it needs to be large enough to really support a professional management company, and we didn't want somebody who was trying to make a quick buck just cram a lot of students into a building and say, look, I've got an on-site manager, and it not be really well done.

113
00:18:45,979 --> 00:18:48,381
[SPEAKER_11]: And no more than two beds per bedroom.

114
00:18:48,421 --> 00:18:54,227
[SPEAKER_11]: We all reminisced about experiences with colleges trying to cram three, four, and five students to a bedroom.

115
00:18:54,668 --> 00:18:57,551
[SPEAKER_11]: And we didn't want people making a profit on that.

116
00:18:58,492 --> 00:19:04,759
[SPEAKER_11]: That the building would have on-site professional management, 24 hours a day, seven days a week, including holidays.

117
00:19:06,260 --> 00:19:15,738
[SPEAKER_11]: and that a management team shall include a property manager, an assistant manager, resident assistants, maintenance staff, and security in numbers sufficient to staff the property.

118
00:19:17,392 --> 00:19:19,313
[SPEAKER_11]: The annual certificate of occupancy.

119
00:19:19,834 --> 00:19:26,018
[SPEAKER_11]: So most buildings only need a certificate of occupancy upon coming online.

120
00:19:26,319 --> 00:19:28,060
[SPEAKER_11]: This would need it annually reviewed.

121
00:19:28,820 --> 00:19:43,251
[SPEAKER_11]: And the application shall include a sworn statement by the owner or authorized manager that the percentage of students enrolled in a university in Medford or Somerville to other residents, where other residents shall not be more than 20%.

122
00:19:45,232 --> 00:19:47,434
[SPEAKER_11]: And I did want to clarify that.

123
00:19:48,134 --> 00:20:02,165
[SPEAKER_11]: We could say that it had to be 100% students, but what we wanted to avoid was the idea that somebody was taking a semester off or they were having trouble paying their bills and they weren't actually enrolled until the last possible minute.

124
00:20:02,645 --> 00:20:06,747
[SPEAKER_11]: And you may know that universities will kick kids out of the dorms for that.

125
00:20:07,467 --> 00:20:09,168
[SPEAKER_11]: You withdraw partway through the semester.

126
00:20:09,228 --> 00:20:09,968
[SPEAKER_11]: You get kicked out.

127
00:20:10,668 --> 00:20:14,910
[SPEAKER_11]: We wanted to allow that those sorts of situations could occur and could stay.

128
00:20:14,930 --> 00:20:18,812
[SPEAKER_11]: The other piece was conceptually that.

129
00:20:19,532 --> 00:20:22,815
[SPEAKER_11]: These have to be students enrolled in a university in Medford or Somerville.

130
00:20:23,375 --> 00:20:28,659
[SPEAKER_11]: But what if you had a good friend enrolled in Northeastern and you wanted to live with them and share an apartment?

131
00:20:29,059 --> 00:20:32,382
[SPEAKER_11]: This would actually be allowed, but only on a small numbers.

132
00:20:32,502 --> 00:20:38,406
[SPEAKER_11]: This would not be a flood of Boston students living in Medford, but it would allow for some exceptions.

133
00:20:38,907 --> 00:20:42,890
[SPEAKER_11]: And then we talked about the fact that there are staff, particularly things like postdocs,

134
00:20:43,370 --> 00:20:48,392
[SPEAKER_11]: who might actually want to stay on in the dorm where they lived when they were a graduate student.

135
00:20:48,772 --> 00:20:50,953
[SPEAKER_11]: So this doesn't say an undergraduate student.

136
00:20:50,993 --> 00:20:52,593
[SPEAKER_11]: You could be a graduate student.

137
00:20:52,953 --> 00:21:00,476
[SPEAKER_11]: And so you might, as a postdoc or a newly graduated student, stay on for a while in the building, but only up to 20%.

138
00:21:01,476 --> 00:21:05,618
[SPEAKER_11]: And that's a negotiable number, but it seems like a rational number.

139
00:21:06,178 --> 00:21:12,540
[SPEAKER_11]: And we looked at that, and we said, well, if it was a 200-person dorm, 200 people, that would be 40 people in the dorm.

140
00:21:13,040 --> 00:21:17,205
[SPEAKER_11]: could be not currently enrolled in Medford or Somerville University.

141
00:21:19,387 --> 00:21:30,959
[SPEAKER_11]: And then the statement would also then go on to talk about the conformity with the operations and management plans, names and telephone numbers of the manager, assistant manager, a 24 by 7 contact.

142
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:35,703
[SPEAKER_11]: Last night we discussed annual fees for the certificate of occupancy.

143
00:21:36,904 --> 00:21:46,710
[SPEAKER_11]: And I think actually upon consideration Danielle and I were discussing we should say that there will be an annual fee to be set by the Community Development Board.

144
00:21:47,010 --> 00:21:59,978
[SPEAKER_11]: We think these numbers are reasonable but we don't like putting fixed numbers in the zoning so that if it seems that this isn't really covering our costs for review we could change them without actually having to change the zoning.

145
00:22:01,427 --> 00:22:04,330
[SPEAKER_11]: And then an operations and management plan has to be presented.

146
00:22:04,350 --> 00:22:13,637
[SPEAKER_11]: And so it is, it says before the hearing with the CDB, that's because this is only through CDB special permit this would be allowed.

147
00:22:14,378 --> 00:22:24,887
[SPEAKER_11]: And that plan would include, I could read it through a bit, locations of entrances and exits, security plan, hours of operations for the staff, including non-residential uses.

148
00:22:26,565 --> 00:22:45,251
[SPEAKER_11]: Any non housing uses on the site would be listed noise control plan location of parking and loading for residents visitors delivery moving centers a waste disposal plan a description of the duties and responsibilities of the staff member by title and a copy of the resident conduct policy and a sample lease agreement.

149
00:22:45,571 --> 00:22:48,592
[SPEAKER_11]: So all that would be given to the city before this building gets approved.

150
00:22:49,585 --> 00:23:02,228
[SPEAKER_11]: And then we said there needs to be a thought about how this could be converted to regular multifamily housing in the event that, you know, it's not working and they feel they need to sell it, et cetera.

151
