00:31:59,822 --> 00:32:06,344
[SPEAKER_04]: Yeah, I just wanted to pick up on what Councilor Scarpelli had just said about oversight.

246
00:32:06,404 --> 00:32:16,387
[SPEAKER_04]: So the way we tried to craft this regulation in regards to the purpose-built student housing specifically was to put in a tremendous amount of oversight.

247
00:32:17,367 --> 00:32:27,030
[SPEAKER_04]: And the certificate of occupancy in this case, whereas Director Hunt said typically you just get one certificate of occupancy when your building's ready to open.

248
00:32:28,246 --> 00:32:32,229
[SPEAKER_04]: In this case, your certificate of occupancy actually has to be renewed every year.

249
00:32:32,790 --> 00:32:37,974
[SPEAKER_04]: You have to make certain representations to the city, so now you're on record that your building's in compliance.

250
00:32:38,795 --> 00:32:53,666
[SPEAKER_04]: And there's a procedure in the regulation such that if we find that you're out of compliance, you can be brought back before the CDB and potentially lose your certificate of occupancy, similar to losing, say, a liquor license.

251
00:32:56,069 --> 00:33:09,499
[SPEAKER_04]: We did try to be very mindful of that because this is a new use and we want to be, everyone to kind of be rest assured that there's going to be proper management which comes from the size of the building.

252
00:33:09,519 --> 00:33:13,382
[SPEAKER_04]: It has to be big enough that they can afford to have proper management and staff.

253
00:33:14,723 --> 00:33:24,571
[SPEAKER_04]: And the regulations kind of hopefully keep them honest and require quite a bit of information from them more so than if someone was building an apartment building, you know,

254
00:33:25,375 --> 00:33:31,398
[SPEAKER_04]: There's management plans and things that are required here that wouldn't be required for someone just building an apartment building.

255
00:33:31,458 --> 00:33:35,981
[SPEAKER_04]: So I think we tried to be thoughtful in this and do a thorough job.

256
00:33:36,021 --> 00:33:41,924
[SPEAKER_04]: And as Director Hunt was going through it, I thought it actually read pretty well on the screen, better than I remembered it.

