1390
02:14:31,485 --> 02:14:36,088
[SPEAKER_10]: Two of those options have an incentivized zoning story?

1391
02:14:36,328 --> 02:14:36,868
[SPEAKER_22]: They all do.

1392
02:14:37,268 --> 02:14:37,848
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay.

1393
02:14:38,049 --> 02:14:39,129
[SPEAKER_22]: Plus one is the incentive.

1394
02:14:39,309 --> 02:14:46,233
[SPEAKER_10]: So I know last night we had a discussion, sorry to turn, about the affordable housing table.

1395
02:14:46,933 --> 02:14:54,877
[SPEAKER_10]: And I'm concerned if we're talking about options with incentivization, but we're still unclear with one of

1396
02:14:55,538 --> 02:14:57,439
[SPEAKER_10]: with one of those options.

1397
02:14:58,499 --> 02:15:04,381
[SPEAKER_10]: Is it wise to continue to discuss these if we're not clear if these options are even applicable?

1398
02:15:04,961 --> 02:15:06,782
[SPEAKER_10]: Is it okay if I ask Danielle that question?

1399
02:15:06,802 --> 02:15:07,822
[SPEAKER_10]: Or Director Hunt?

1400
02:15:07,882 --> 02:15:09,703
[SPEAKER_22]: I would like to hear Danielle and Alicia, their response.

1401
02:15:09,743 --> 02:15:10,763
[SPEAKER_22]: It's a fair question.

1402
02:15:16,465 --> 02:15:21,947
[SPEAKER_11]: So if I understand your question, it's if we're removing one of the major, so,

1403
02:15:23,767 --> 02:15:28,092
[SPEAKER_11]: The proposal on the table is we either would fix the incentives.

1404
02:15:28,112 --> 02:15:35,299
[SPEAKER_11]: There's a problem with the incentive for affordable housing and that can't be done tonight.

1405
02:15:35,359 --> 02:15:46,711
[SPEAKER_11]: It's going to take us a little bit of time to work through the math and the scenarios to figure out how to incentivize affordable housing in a way that's worth it to the city so that we get the height we want and the units.

1406
02:15:49,313 --> 02:15:55,717
[SPEAKER_11]: So if it was adopted tonight, we would have to take that section out because it is a major loophole.

1407
02:15:56,057 --> 02:15:59,799
[SPEAKER_11]: And we don't want people applying and building with the major loophole in there.

1408
02:16:01,521 --> 02:16:03,242
[SPEAKER_11]: And it leaves other incentives.

1409
02:16:03,262 --> 02:16:07,765
[SPEAKER_11]: Other incentives are still there, but they're not as attractive to people in general.

1410
02:16:08,785 --> 02:16:12,087
[SPEAKER_11]: They're less likely to be picked up, particularly in the BA1.

1411
02:16:13,068 --> 02:16:16,789
[SPEAKER_11]: The other incentives are really unlikely that anybody would use them.

1412
02:16:17,529 --> 02:16:21,570
[SPEAKER_11]: So the affordable housing is truly the only real incentive for this area.

1413
02:16:23,011 --> 02:16:29,013
[SPEAKER_11]: So the two options on the table are to basically adopt it.

1414
02:16:30,533 --> 02:16:39,298
[SPEAKER_11]: without that in it soon or continue working on this the staff need and the consultants through the summer to sort of figure this out.

1415
02:16:39,338 --> 02:16:52,487
[SPEAKER_11]: We need a couple of weeks which basically takes us through the summer to bring it back in September at which point we believe that we can do incentivized affordable housing to do these incentives and that that would work.

1416
02:16:53,587 --> 02:16:56,589
[SPEAKER_11]: But we can't adopt that tonight like we don't have the ability to.

1417
02:16:58,370 --> 02:17:04,452
[SPEAKER_11]: So if one was to leave it with the incentives, then it would just not get used.

1418
02:17:05,372 --> 02:17:09,614
[SPEAKER_11]: If say it was passed tonight, nobody would take the incentives.

1419
02:17:10,094 --> 02:17:13,115
[SPEAKER_11]: And they may or may not propose something over the course of the summer.

1420
02:17:13,555 --> 02:17:21,297
[SPEAKER_11]: A savvy developer would say, yeah, but the city is putting better incentives in in the fall that we want to use, and we'll wait.

1421
02:17:23,398 --> 02:17:25,179
[SPEAKER_11]: So that's kind of how I see it.

1422
02:17:25,619 --> 02:17:39,983
[SPEAKER_11]: Either, right, it's adopted without it and developers will wait and things in this area won't happen or we adopt it all in the fall with the incentives in there, in which case there are meaningful incentives for people to use.

1423
02:17:40,003 --> 02:17:41,543
[SPEAKER_08]: I just want to be clear.

1424
02:17:41,563 --> 02:17:44,024
[SPEAKER_08]: We're not talking about adopting any zoning tonight, right?

1425
02:17:46,063 --> 02:18:05,469
[SPEAKER_08]: If what we're talking with the choice before us is to close a public hearing which then starts a clock for the city board to make a recommendation and the city board can make a recommendation that we should update the incentive and that would there would be time to then update the incentive or the city board can make a recommendation to remove the incentive.

1426
02:18:05,569 --> 02:18:10,270
[SPEAKER_08]: But I just wanted to clarify like we can't vote tonight to adopt the zoning.

1427
02:18:10,390 --> 02:18:14,792
[SPEAKER_08]: We're not adopting final zoning at any point tonight because that's,

1428
02:18:16,232 --> 02:18:17,233
[SPEAKER_08]: It's just not possible.

1429
02:18:17,493 --> 02:18:17,693
[SPEAKER_11]: Right.

1430
02:18:17,853 --> 02:18:20,214
[SPEAKER_11]: Thank you for clarifying that.

1431
02:18:20,614 --> 02:18:22,295
[SPEAKER_11]: Nothing would get adopted tonight.

1432
02:18:23,036 --> 02:18:27,978
[SPEAKER_11]: If the hearing was closed tonight, they would stop taking public hearing.

1433
02:18:28,559 --> 02:18:34,202
[SPEAKER_11]: The CD board would have technically 20 days, and then the city council could vote after that.

1434
02:18:34,562 --> 02:18:36,603
[SPEAKER_11]: But the city council doesn't have to vote.

1435
02:18:36,803 --> 02:18:42,987
[SPEAKER_11]: The city council could wait until the CD board comes with its recommendation on how to do this.

1436
02:18:44,027 --> 02:18:46,729
[SPEAKER_11]: There just wouldn't be any further comment on that.

1437
02:18:47,870 --> 02:18:51,393
[SPEAKER_11]: In the terms of the incentive housing, I'm going to say it's super technical.

1438
02:18:51,853 --> 02:18:57,076
[SPEAKER_11]: Like, I can't imagine that anybody other than a lawyer or a mathematician is going to end up with comments on it.

1439
02:18:58,277 --> 02:19:01,740
[SPEAKER_11]: We would publish sort of, here's the table, this is why we think this works.

1440
02:19:02,981 --> 02:19:10,048
[SPEAKER_11]: I don't know, given vacations and stuff, that we could do that in 20 days to put it in front of the CD board that soon.

1441
02:19:10,769 --> 02:19:12,711
[SPEAKER_11]: Could we put it in front of the CD board in August?

1442
02:19:13,032 --> 02:19:14,653
[SPEAKER_11]: I think that's rational.

1443
02:19:16,475 --> 02:19:19,418
[SPEAKER_11]: But yeah, that's kind of where we would stand with it.

1444
02:19:20,640 --> 02:19:21,480
[SPEAKER_11]: Danielle wants to add to it.

1445
02:19:21,500 --> 02:19:24,524
[SPEAKER_11]: So I'm going to say that Danielle and some of our interns have been studying this a lot.

1446
02:19:30,411 --> 02:19:32,012
[SPEAKER_34]: Yes, thanks Paige for bringing that up.

1447
02:19:32,032 --> 02:19:42,957
[SPEAKER_34]: Yeah, I feel very strongly that this needs to be fixed so that we can actually get deeper affordability and additional affordable units.

1448
02:19:43,718 --> 02:19:53,882
[SPEAKER_34]: I think it'd be a real shame if because of two months we have to delete these and either properties are redeveloped and

1449
02:19:57,063 --> 02:19:58,685
[SPEAKER_34]: And we missed these opportunities.

1450
02:19:59,145 --> 02:20:01,567
[SPEAKER_34]: But I did want to ask a question about the timing.

1451
02:20:01,607 --> 02:20:07,493
[SPEAKER_34]: I believe that the City Board does not have, if they didn't close their public hearing, then the clock doesn't start.

1452
02:20:08,934 --> 02:20:19,544
[SPEAKER_34]: Because the order of operations is that the City Board has a public hearing and then they close their public hearing and make a recommendation to the City Council.

1453
02:20:22,063 --> 02:20:28,528
[SPEAKER_34]: That's when the shot clock starts when they close a public hearing if they keep it open then it's still open.

1454
02:20:28,568 --> 02:20:32,531
[SPEAKER_34]: There's no clock just because city council closes their public hearing.

1455
02:20:34,333 --> 02:20:34,593
[SPEAKER_08]: Right.

1456
02:20:35,233 --> 02:20:37,955
[SPEAKER_08]: I mean I think and maybe we should just go the other direction here.

1457
02:20:37,995 --> 02:20:43,299
[SPEAKER_08]: I was thinking we could talk about the substance and then talk about the process but it sounds like we're in the process.

1458
02:20:43,339 --> 02:20:46,342
[SPEAKER_34]: I just wanted to clarify that because it was brought up.

1459
02:20:47,598 --> 02:20:50,441
[SPEAKER_08]: Yes, well, no, and I think that that was my point, right?

1460
02:20:50,501 --> 02:20:54,945
[SPEAKER_08]: We, the decision tonight is do we want to continue a public hearing?

1461
02:20:54,985 --> 02:20:56,286
[SPEAKER_08]: Do we want to close a public hearing?

1462
02:20:56,306 --> 02:20:57,848
[SPEAKER_08]: Do we all want to make the same choice on that?

1463
02:20:57,888 --> 02:20:59,429
[SPEAKER_08]: Do we want to make different choices on that?

1464
02:21:00,710 --> 02:21:12,922
[SPEAKER_08]: I think something that we have heard pretty consistently from folks is there's been a lot of meetings and we did outline a process in January and then an updated process in March and April.

1465
02:21:13,882 --> 02:21:18,346
[SPEAKER_08]: indicating like what would be the ways to, for people to participate in this process.

1466
02:21:19,788 --> 02:21:30,898
[SPEAKER_08]: If we continue the public hearing, then we continue asking people to come back and attend more and more meetings and make comments again, feel either obligated or interested in continuing to do that.

1467
02:21:34,281 --> 02:21:37,224
[SPEAKER_08]: I was, I think there's a couple of ways that we could go tonight.

1468
02:21:38,895 --> 02:21:48,459
[SPEAKER_08]: We could all continue public hearings if we do that, then we can't really have a joint meeting on this until the fall because the mayor said I don't want you to have public meetings on zoning during the summer.

1469
02:21:50,572 --> 02:22:08,499
[SPEAKER_08]: We could both close a public hearing tonight if we agree on the substance of the height and the purpose-built student housing proposals, like if we agree in principle that these are things we want to do, these are generally the heights that we want to have, and what needs to happen next is the technical elements of what is the actual language.

1470
02:22:09,319 --> 02:22:12,160
[SPEAKER_08]: I certainly think that the Community Development Board could meet over the summer

1471
02:22:13,202 --> 02:22:16,443
[SPEAKER_08]: to finalize the incentive technicality.

1472
02:22:16,463 --> 02:22:18,984
[SPEAKER_08]: Like I think we all agree we want an affordable housing incentive, right?

1473
02:22:19,024 --> 02:22:20,005
[SPEAKER_08]: That, we agree on that.

1474
02:22:20,065 --> 02:22:21,045
[SPEAKER_08]: That's the substance.

1475
02:22:22,726 --> 02:22:32,250
[SPEAKER_08]: Like it's just that there's a technical issue where on small projects with a lower number of units, we're having math problems.

1476
02:22:32,270 --> 02:22:32,790
[SPEAKER_08]: So, you know,

1477
02:22:33,694 --> 02:22:35,696
[SPEAKER_08]: We all agree that we want an affordable housing incentive.

1478
02:22:35,736 --> 02:22:40,380
[SPEAKER_08]: Do we need to continue the public hearing to get more public feedback on something we already all agree on?

1479
02:22:40,581 --> 02:22:43,724
[SPEAKER_08]: I think that's just kind of the principle that I'm trying to put out there.

1480
02:22:45,205 --> 02:22:49,109
[SPEAKER_08]: So I think we could all agree to continue the public hearing.

1481
02:22:50,127 --> 02:22:51,908
[SPEAKER_08]: and push this out for several months.

1482
02:22:52,509 --> 02:23:11,662
[SPEAKER_08]: I think we could agree for both bodies to close the public hearing if we agree after discussion on the substantive process that we're in a general consensus on heights in the sub-districts and in a general consensus that the purpose-built definition that you all really worked on last night is something that we all agree to and then

1483
02:23:12,580 --> 02:23:19,726
[SPEAKER_08]: you and PDS, the city board and PDS could work out the technical final version of the recommendations that you were to submit to us.

1484
02:23:21,387 --> 02:23:29,333
[SPEAKER_08]: If we're concerned about the shot clock, I'm sure that we could agree as part of the vote that we're not going to schedule a vote until we receive recommendations from you guys.

1485
02:23:29,613 --> 02:23:34,797
[SPEAKER_08]: As the person who puts things on the agenda, I can say I won't put it on the agenda until we receive recommendations from you guys.

1486
02:23:34,817 --> 02:23:36,979
[SPEAKER_08]: So I don't want us to get caught in that piece of this.

1487
02:23:36,999 --> 02:23:40,442
[SPEAKER_08]: Because it's, yes, closing the public hearing,

1488
02:23:41,400 --> 02:23:43,221
[SPEAKER_08]: starts a nominally starts a shot clock.

1489
02:23:45,422 --> 02:23:50,325
[SPEAKER_08]: But it also gives certainty to the public about what the rest of this process is going to look like.

1490
02:23:50,465 --> 02:23:56,549
[SPEAKER_08]: And if per the mayor's directive we're going to continue the public hearing it means

1491
02:23:57,517 --> 02:24:01,039
[SPEAKER_08]: there will be no recommendations until September or maybe even October.

1492
02:24:01,159 --> 02:24:05,522
[SPEAKER_08]: And I think we should really consider whether that's the timeline and the process that we want to have here.

1493
02:24:05,542 --> 02:24:16,129
[SPEAKER_08]: Because I think there's a way for us to have continued discussions to get it right, to get the text of this right, if we all agree largely on the intent and the substance of the decisions that we have to make.

1494
02:24:17,360 --> 02:24:20,422
[SPEAKER_08]: That allows for the CD board and PDS to work over the summer.

1495
02:24:21,783 --> 02:24:27,587
[SPEAKER_08]: And I think that can happen if we're saying we've closed public hearings because that's what the mayor said we shouldn't be doing over the summer is having public hearings.

1496
02:24:29,108 --> 02:24:31,350
[SPEAKER_08]: If we choose to keep it open, then I think

1497
02:24:33,212 --> 02:24:35,475
[SPEAKER_08]: We're just going to be months, months out from here.

1498
02:24:36,616 --> 02:24:42,081
[SPEAKER_08]: And I do think, frankly, you know, we'll hear maybe from councilors and CD board members a disagreement.

1499
02:24:42,762 --> 02:24:46,345
[SPEAKER_08]: Maybe the council says we do want to close the public hearing, maybe the CD board says we don't.

1500
02:24:49,308 --> 02:24:58,731
[SPEAKER_08]: then I think you guys would have a process on your own and you would have maybe some more public hearings and then you would come up with recommendations and then whatever you recommend would come back to us.

1501
02:24:58,851 --> 02:25:08,635
[SPEAKER_08]: But that would be more akin to the process that we had last time where I think there was council disagreed with some recommendations and chose not to adopt them.

1502
02:25:08,675 --> 02:25:13,416
[SPEAKER_08]: I think something we've been trying to do in this process is to avoid that, to try to have consensus with both boards.

1503
02:25:14,777 --> 02:25:18,418
[SPEAKER_08]: So I do think that if we take two paths here, we might be in a situation where,

1504
02:25:20,373 --> 02:25:27,637
[SPEAKER_08]: A lot of some public hearings and work and recommendations are made and then it comes back to the council and the council says well we agree with six out of eight of them.

1505
02:25:27,877 --> 02:25:29,538
[SPEAKER_08]: And so I would like to try to avoid that.

1506
02:25:30,878 --> 02:25:38,102
[SPEAKER_08]: My personal opinion again is that I think if we were to if we agree on the heights and the major decisions that we have tonight.

1507
02:25:39,937 --> 02:25:50,626
[SPEAKER_08]: would be to say that the public hearing process is concluded tonight, but that the CD board and the PDS team could work on finalizing the recommendation language over the next couple of months.

1508
02:25:52,268 --> 02:25:53,449
[SPEAKER_08]: That's my personal opinion.

1509
02:25:53,769 --> 02:25:55,851
[SPEAKER_08]: People probably disagree with me.

1510
02:25:56,992 --> 02:25:57,812
[SPEAKER_22]: That's TBD.

1511
02:25:58,513 --> 02:26:00,655
[SPEAKER_22]: I believe, Paige, you still have the floor.

1512
02:26:00,695 --> 02:26:04,538
[SPEAKER_22]: You have one question, and it took only 12 minutes to get answered, but that's cool.

1513
02:26:04,798 --> 02:26:07,681
[SPEAKER_10]: So unsure of the process, even though we're not supposed to say that.

1514
02:26:08,695 --> 02:26:10,917
[SPEAKER_22]: We're making it up as we go along.

1515
02:26:13,098 --> 02:26:16,081
[SPEAKER_08]: That I would not endorse, that statement.

1516
02:26:16,381 --> 02:26:18,742
[SPEAKER_08]: I think we have options and we're deciding on them.

1517
02:26:25,287 --> 02:26:27,329
[SPEAKER_10]: So what are we doing?

1518
02:26:28,750 --> 02:26:29,050
[SPEAKER_10]: Am I?

1519
02:26:30,231 --> 02:26:34,274
[SPEAKER_08]: I mean, if we want to talk about, if we want to pick a path or do you want to talk about the BA 1?

1520
02:26:34,734 --> 02:26:35,555
[SPEAKER_10]: I would love to pick a path.

1521
02:26:36,114 --> 02:26:37,955
[SPEAKER_08]: All right, so we want to talk about process.

1522
02:26:39,236 --> 02:26:39,757
[SPEAKER_10]: Yes, please.

1523
02:26:41,998 --> 02:26:48,783
[SPEAKER_08]: Well, yeah, I mean, we could go to the council if counselors have a preference for how we move forward.

1524
02:26:48,823 --> 02:26:51,905
[SPEAKER_08]: Or Doug, if you want to talk with the CD board about how you think you'd like to move forward.

1525
02:26:52,546 --> 02:26:55,888
[SPEAKER_08]: And then we can come back and talk, try to agree on the heights and the student housing definition.

1526
02:27:00,494 --> 02:27:02,735
[SPEAKER_22]: I guess I'm hesitant.

1527
02:27:03,855 --> 02:27:08,677
[SPEAKER_22]: I think the process, in my opinion, would grow out of largely if there's consensus.

1528
02:27:09,057 --> 02:27:09,257
[SPEAKER_22]: All right.

1529
02:27:09,357 --> 02:27:12,238
[SPEAKER_22]: If there's not consensus, the process is going to be different.

1530
02:27:13,419 --> 02:27:19,381
[SPEAKER_22]: And that's why I think and I appreciated the comments about the BA1 because it's clearly some consensus over here.

1531
02:27:20,482 --> 02:27:30,550
[SPEAKER_22]: I would like to know if there is over here too, because I think to chair bears earlier comments, if there is consensus, it's going to be easier to get to the finish line.

1532
02:27:31,410 --> 02:27:34,533
[SPEAKER_22]: But if there's not, I think we're talking about September.

1533
02:27:35,113 --> 02:27:36,434
[SPEAKER_22]: That's just the way I see it.

1534
02:27:36,635 --> 02:27:39,297
[SPEAKER_22]: But I, I don't know where you guys stand on this.

1535
02:27:39,337 --> 02:27:43,440
[SPEAKER_22]: We didn't talk at all last night about heights and massing and we've had,

1536
02:27:44,067 --> 02:27:48,256
[SPEAKER_22]: I know, look, I proposed five stories for the BA-1, and then I pulled it back after thinking about it.

1537
02:27:48,316 --> 02:27:49,740
[SPEAKER_22]: So there's been evolution.

1538
02:27:49,780 --> 02:27:50,642
[SPEAKER_22]: There's back and forth.

1539
02:27:51,832 --> 02:27:55,633
[SPEAKER_22]: the new option with the five on the corners, I'd have no idea what anybody thinks about that.

1540
02:27:55,793 --> 02:28:03,695
[SPEAKER_22]: And that's why I think at least getting a sense of that would help, it might simplify the process or not.

1541
02:28:04,295 --> 02:28:19,639
[SPEAKER_22]: So I guess I would ask you to, and if you agree, to make a request, make a sense of your direction for each one of these zones to see if there is consensus here, because that will, in my mind, change the process.

1542
02:28:20,339 --> 02:28:21,559
[SPEAKER_22]: So let me go back to...

1543
02:28:23,460 --> 02:28:33,044
[SPEAKER_22]: Go ahead, Paige, again.

1544
02:28:33,104 --> 02:28:33,744
[SPEAKER_10]: Thank you, Jay Carr.

1545
02:28:34,084 --> 02:28:38,126
[SPEAKER_10]: So I will go with, I don't know if we want to put the options back on for the public?

1546
02:28:38,146 --> 02:28:42,828
[SPEAKER_22]: Yeah, let's put the options back on screen for the BA1, if that's okay, just so everyone can see what we're talking about.

1547
02:28:42,848 --> 02:28:45,529
[SPEAKER_22]: It's like, let's make a deal.

1548
02:28:55,443 --> 02:29:04,048
[SPEAKER_10]: As a resident and business owner that is on this strip, I will go with option A, specifically because I look at that corner every day, and I love that corner.

1549
02:29:04,448 --> 02:29:06,269
[SPEAKER_10]: And it's really tricky to turn.

1550
02:29:06,729 --> 02:29:10,691
[SPEAKER_10]: If you're coming from Boston Ave to take a right up Winthrop, you're going up a hill.

1551
02:29:10,711 --> 02:29:13,853
[SPEAKER_10]: So I go with option A. Okay.

1552
02:29:25,989 --> 02:29:27,009
[SPEAKER_22]: Dina, would you like to go next?

1553
02:29:29,670 --> 02:29:31,310
[SPEAKER_16]: Emily, could you do me a favor?

1554
02:29:31,350 --> 02:29:33,071
[SPEAKER_16]: Could you show the shadow study again?

1555
02:29:33,091 --> 02:29:34,651
[SPEAKER_16]: And I think it's important.

1556
02:29:34,711 --> 02:29:45,613
[SPEAKER_16]: Someone said, one of the comments for the four plus one and the extra, is that we give a little geography lesson of what we're looking at too.

1557
02:29:47,254 --> 02:29:49,714
[SPEAKER_16]: Because hillside hardware isn't a hill, I agree with you.

1558
02:29:49,794 --> 02:29:52,575
[SPEAKER_16]: I've walked the area many, many times.

1559
02:29:55,000 --> 02:29:56,382
[SPEAKER_16]: There's a little house, too.

1560
02:29:57,282 --> 02:29:58,463
[SPEAKER_16]: It's not just tracks.

1561
02:29:58,563 --> 02:30:00,505
[SPEAKER_16]: There's some residential houses back there, too.

1562
02:30:05,409 --> 02:30:05,609
[SPEAKER_16]: Yeah?

1563
02:30:06,670 --> 02:30:07,170
[SPEAKER_22]: Go ahead, Emily.

1564
02:30:07,190 --> 02:30:07,551
[SPEAKER_15]: Thank you.

1565
02:30:07,571 --> 02:30:09,332
[SPEAKER_15]: Can I just confirm?

1566
02:30:09,432 --> 02:30:14,836
[SPEAKER_15]: So we have a shadow study for the 3 plus 1 and the 3 plus 1 and the 4 plus 1.

1567
02:30:14,896 --> 02:30:15,937
[SPEAKER_15]: Which do you want to see?

1568
02:30:16,498 --> 02:30:18,640
[SPEAKER_16]: All of them.

1569
02:30:18,660 --> 02:30:19,780
[SPEAKER_16]: 3 plus 1 I'm fine with.

1570
02:30:19,840 --> 02:30:24,064
[SPEAKER_16]: But look at 4.1 and then look at the small house behind Danish Pastry.

1571
02:30:24,470 --> 02:30:26,813
[SPEAKER_15]: So we don't have a 4 plus 1 shot.

1572
02:30:26,833 --> 02:30:27,174
[SPEAKER_15]: We can do 3, 1.

1573
02:30:27,695 --> 02:30:28,195
[SPEAKER_15]: OK.

1574
02:30:28,476 --> 02:30:28,616
[SPEAKER_16]: Yeah.

1575
02:30:29,037 --> 02:30:29,678
[SPEAKER_16]: That one's fine.

1576
02:30:30,739 --> 02:30:31,040
[SPEAKER_15]: OK.

1577
02:30:32,422 --> 02:30:33,042
[SPEAKER_16]: See that house?

1578
02:30:35,145 --> 02:30:37,168
[SPEAKER_16]: And I guess the question someone brought up.

1579
02:30:38,017 --> 02:30:43,859
[SPEAKER_16]: Will the 45 degree angle be implemented for that small house behind Danish Pastry?

1580
02:30:43,899 --> 02:30:45,980
[SPEAKER_15]: You're talking about this house here?

1581
02:30:46,561 --> 02:30:47,581
[SPEAKER_15]: Yes.

1582
02:30:47,821 --> 02:30:53,403
[SPEAKER_15]: So the 45 degree angle is when the building is abutting a residential area.

1583
02:30:54,024 --> 02:30:57,685
[SPEAKER_15]: That building is included within the BANCD.

1584
02:30:57,885 --> 02:31:02,047
[SPEAKER_15]: So the 45 degree angle would not be applicable to that house.

1585
02:31:02,547 --> 02:31:04,468
[SPEAKER_16]: But someone lives in that house, I think.

1586
02:31:04,668 --> 02:31:05,308
[SPEAKER_15]: Of course, yes.

1587
02:31:09,343 --> 02:31:12,008
[SPEAKER_16]: And then, OK, so that's what I wanted to point out.

1588
02:31:12,349 --> 02:31:16,617
[SPEAKER_16]: So I'm going to go with the first option, option A.

1589
02:31:18,140 --> 02:31:18,660
[SPEAKER_16]: The 3-1.

1590
02:31:19,161 --> 02:31:25,884
[SPEAKER_16]: And the reason why is that if you look at what we did for Meffitt Square, Meffitt Square was pretty much flat.

1591
02:31:26,284 --> 02:31:34,888
[SPEAKER_16]: If you look at the high street area on the corner, if you look from high street across the street, they're pretty much flat.

1592
02:31:34,928 --> 02:31:39,590
[SPEAKER_16]: And I think we did like 4.1 or 3 plus 1 on Meffitt Square.

1593
02:31:40,371 --> 02:31:41,531
[SPEAKER_16]: But the street's wider.

1594
